 :tx/rationale "DEFECT-002+003 architectural context: Two findings are design limitations, not implementation bugs. DEFECT-002 (stale count under concurrent writers in observe.rs:654-727) arises because two simultaneous braid observe processes could both read old_count=N for the same concept and both write N+1 instead of N+2. This is inherent to the embedded single-writer store model (ADR-STORE-006) and will be resolved by the daemon architecture. DEFECT-003 (O(C^2*N) in co_occurrence_matrix at concept.rs:470-497) is acceptable at current scale (5-15 concepts, 10-50 observations) but will need index acceleration at Stage 3 (100+ concepts). Neither blocks Session 045 or the dogfood run. Document as known limitations."
